âœ… Interpretation:

    Low MAD (e.g., < 0.015) â†’ actual distribution is very close to Benford's Law (often seen in forensic/accounting audits).

    High MAD â†’ indicates a deviation from expected distribution, suggesting the data does not follow Benford's Law.

